metadata.name: a reveure! #70
metadata.description:
‘a reveure!’ is a catalan farewell expression. this collection is a souvenir to celebrate me meeting up with artists, collectors and friends during 2023’s summer art events (Responsive Dreams in Barcelona and NFT Show Europe in Valencia). 
mechanics to get a piece: say ‘hi’ and chat with me to get a free pass to mint your iteration and its signed miniprint. i’ll be doing mobile live minting on small screen (iPad/phone) during Barcelona and Valencia events. 

‘a reveure!’ is about simplifying my painting brushes style used in previous works, in an attempt to find minimalist and more conceptual approach. using only black and white and minimizing the use of random, i explore the void and the spaces generated on the canvas, discovering how abstract sculpture-like figures emerge. raw edges and big brushes make the eye confused as it seems 3D shapes building up. 

this line of work and the concept behind it was inspired by Elena Asins’ computer art from late XX’s century.

the motion restarts every 20sec
press [s] or click/touch to save an image
press [r] to reload 
press [1] - [9] to make higher resolution
press [c] to make brushes spin
press left/right arrows to move brushes left/right

made with love and p5js

thank you fxhash team to give me the opportunity and tools to do this special mobile live minting

Marc L Clapers / mekhno
summer 2023

metadata.name: Skravert #71
metadata.description:
‘Skravert’ - Norwegian, verb, past tense. ‘The act of filling an area with lines; to shade an area’.

Skravert is a series of 320 sketches, each capturing the texture and feel of a material residing somewhere between cardboard and woolen rugs. The project is centred around rectangle subdivision and a line drawing algorithm, giving each piece its own unique expression when combined with a selection of 28 different color  palettes.  

Original artwork by perkwerk * made with p5.js * 2021

metadata.name: Dencity #722
metadata.description:
Dencity is a generative art project inspired by aerial views of cities with a high density of buildings. Its perspective effect, its perfectly imprecise lines, its subtle textures and its very advanced level of detail give it the appearance of a hand-drawn work.

Behind the visible art (the image) hides another form of art, an extremely complex algorithm capable of calculating and drawing in 2D each variation of the Dencity project. To draw a variation, the algorithm notably takes around 3,000,000 to 20,000,000 random decisions based on the hash of the mint and draws around 800,000 to 4,000,000 lines to create all the strokes and texture effects.

Made with ❤️, code and p5js.

metadata.name: The Past Ahead #254
metadata.description:
Cyanotypes once were the most advanced technology to create images. When I see one today I look at it as a beautiful relic and I can't help but put my present in perspective. In these uncertain times the technologies we use to create are threatened with sudden extinction. But I feel joy in imagining our works joining the strata of history, a fallen species, the breeding ground of creations to come.

Controls :

• Press 1, 2, 3, or 4 to make a capture and download a PNG with a resolution of x1, x2, x3 or x4.

———————

The Past Ahead by Ferdinand Dervieux, 2022
Made with Unity

metadata.name: Dialog Box #155
metadata.description:
Dialog Box is a playful generative art project that invites viewers to engage with the concept of choice in the digital age. Inspired by the early Mac OS, the artwork presents an interface of two buttons, each symbolizing a choice steeped in 80s and 90s pop culture, from the serious to the lighthearted.

https://medium.com/@duaneking/dialog-box-by-duane-king-scott-brewer-and-adam-moliski-abab7afd3519
